pageContext.claim: “But through Operation Warp Speed, we're on track to have 100 million vaccine doses before the end of this year.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump repeatedly claimed 100 million doses of a coronavirus vaccine would be delivered by the end of 2020. But that turned out to be false. As of Dec. 30, according to a dashboard maintained by the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, only 12.4 million doses are had been distributed and 2.8 million people had received the first dose of the two-dose requirement.
